  "text": "The mean intensity of the NQO1 bands was 13 Ϯ 6 (means Ϯ SE) times greater for the hyperoxia-exposed than the normoxic cells for the 5 cell pairs studied. There were no detectable corresponding bands in the same region of the blots when control, nonspecific IgG1 was used in the place of ␣-NQO1 antibody. Human recombinant NQO1 was the standard. Cytosolic fractions were prepared from 3 each normoxic and hyperoxiaexposed cell cultures, and NAD(P)H:quinone oxidoreductase 1 (NQO1) activity was determined as described in MATERIALS AND METHODS. *Significantly different from normoxic cells without dicumarol (P Ͻ 0.05, t-test). Because DQH 2 is highly cell membrane permeant and the reaction between the ferricyanide and DQH 2 is instantaneous on the study time scale, ferricyanide acts as a sink for virtually all the cell-generated DQH 2 [CITATION_1] . Thus the contribution of cell-mediated DQH 2 oxidation is assumed to be eliminated when ferricyanide is present, and the ferricyanide reduction rate in the presence of DQ is given in Eq. 9, derived from Eqs. 5-8, as described in Ref. [CITATION_2] ",
